		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message33162333">A deconstruction of deconstructions is a hilarious idea but I can't think of any example because I don't think deconstruction by itself has become mainstream enough for a work to make a huge impact via a plot twist within a plot twist. (Maybe if NGE ended with TOAST it would've been a deconstruction of deconstructions, before most deconstructions were existent to deconstruct(!).)</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
